<span class="headers">July 30, 2003 - Glerp!!!</span>
<p>
As most, if not all of you, have noticed by now, things were crazier than usual around here for the last couple days.<p>
We ended up moving the boards to a new software package to handle the myriad of bugs that we couldn't address before. The timing sort of took me by surprise, but we're managing.  95% of everything came over just fine, but the other 5% is causing some problems.  (Avatar sizes are still only half-fixed, the nav buttons are gone, the logo needs replacing, and so forth.) We'll get there, but, it will take time, especially with other stuff going on in our lives.<p>
The hard-working folks at Racknine also realized we weren't joking about the extra load when the database went live. We apologize for some flakiness today as they copied the site over to a new server (with newer SQL server software for more "oomph" as well), and then flipped the DNS over. I lost edit access for a bit, as did all the folks doing updates to the site, but we should be good now ... I hope.<p>
I do apologize for all the chaos due to growing pains and the like, and we'll continue our clean-up efforts over the next week or two. This wasn't as seamless as we'd like, but the longer we waited on getting all this out the door, the more likely it was that it would never get done, and I'd just shelve the whole site. :/ I suspect that most of you would be a tad unhappy with that option, so we muddle along as best we can. {tired grin}</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">July 25, 2003 - Stray Updates</span>
<p>
Just a few things, before I finally go get some sleep.<p>
<ul><li>The mass enchant spells for cultural metals (adamantite, mithril, steel, brellium) are currently not working as intended. It is fixed on Test. Unfortunately, even after more than one warning from EQTC staff, the message board thread regarding this issue degenerated into SoE-bashing, and will not be revived, so take this as your warning that there's a problem until the next patch.</li>
<li>The serverwide.eqtraders channel is pretty much MIA. Someone passworded it, nobody seems to know who did it or what the new password is. Since I've never had (nor wanted) ownership of that chat channel, there's not a lot I can do about it. There's a <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=9437">message board thread</a> discussing alternative channel possibilities.</li>
<li>The database forum is up and running. Again, I ask that you please keep the commentary there, and NOT in DenMother's Corner, direct PMs to me, etc. I'm feeling very extremely overloaded, if you couldn't tell from the last front page update from me, and I am literally cringing every time I hit the boards right now. Please, folks, ease up on the PMs, the feature requests we've already said to WAIT on, and such.</li>
<li>Gukta trade supplies fell through a crack, and I've not slept in about 22 hours. I'll finish them after sleep.</li></ul>
I want to add my thanks to Ngreth's to all of you who have helped make this database a reality. I'm not coherent enough to go through a list without missing someone and likely offending them horribly, so I'll just say a huge thank you to all of you at once for now.  {exhausted halfling hugs}</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>

		Last Modified on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
